\n    {\n        $realPath = str_replace(\'\\\\\', \'/\', $this->fileDriver->getRealPath($path));\n        if (!is_array($directories)) {\n            $directories = (array)$directories;\n        }\n        foreach ($directories as $directory) {\n            if (0 === strpos($realPath, $directory)) {\n                return true;\n            }\n        }\n        return false;\n    }</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If You can\'t find out the (/vendor/magento/framework/) folder in magento 2.2.7 - 2.3.3 . Then You can check it here:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>#lib\\internal\\Magento\\Framework\\View\\Element\\Template\\File\\Validator.php</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->', 'Magento Admin panel blank page', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '263-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-03-31 09:22:05', '2020-03-31 09:22:05', '', 263, 'https://www.ayushshrestha.com.np/263-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(267, 1, '2020-03-31 09:22:14', '2020-03-31 09:22:14', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> This is a Magento bug. Wrong paths to Windows are generated. The fixed fix is </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Magento 2.3.0 - 2.3.3</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Go to </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>vendor/magento/framework/View/Element/Template/File/Validator.php:140</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>the string</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>if (0 === strpos($realPath, $directory)) {\n    return true;\n}</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>to replace</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>$realDirectory = $this->fileDriver->getRealPath($directory);\nif ($realDirectory &amp;&amp; 0 === strpos($realPath, $realDirectory)) {\n   return true;\n}</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Magento 2.2.7</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>/vendor/magento/framework/View/Element/Template/File/Validator.php:113</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>code</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>protected function isPathInDirectories($path, $directories)\n{\n    if (!is_array($directories)) {\n        $directories = (array)$directories;\n    }\n    foreach ($directories as $directory) {\n        if (0 === strpos($this->fileDriver->getRealPath($path), $directory)) {\n            return true;\n        }\n    }\n    return false;\n}</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>to replace</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>protected function isPathInDirectories($path, $directories)\n    {\n        $realPath = str_replace(\'\\\\\', \'/\', $this->fileDriver->getRealPath($path));\n        if (!is_array($directories)) {\n            $directories = (array)$directories;\n        }\n        foreach ($directories as $directory) {\n            if (0 === strpos($realPath, $directory)) {\n                return true;\n            }\n        }\n        return false;\n    }</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If You can\'t find out the (/vendor/magento/framework/) folder in magento 2.2.7 - 2.3.3 . Then You can check it here:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>#lib\\internal\\Magento\\Framework\\View\\Element\\Template\\File\\Validator.php</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->', 'Magento Admin panel blank page', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '263-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-03-31 09:22:14', '2020-03-31 09:22:14', '', 263, 'https://www.ayushshrestha.com.np/263-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(269, 1, '2020-04-18 13:56:31', '2020-04-18 13:56:31', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solved: Blank Issue Magento 2.2.7 and 2.3 Admin</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Magento 2 CMS is an effective platform for the running of e-commerce companies and can be managed via the admin panel. Admin is responsible for the store\'s functionalities and any errors in the admin panel are unacceptable. However, after updating or installing Magento 2.2.7 and Magento 2.3, the clients faced the question of the blank page in the admin panel!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We fixed this problem and have agreed to publish it as a workaround for all Magento 2.2.7 and Magento 2.3 store owners.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you have downloaded or updated the new version recently and face the blank issue of the Magento 2.2.7 and 2.3 admin page, as shown below, follow the solution given in the article.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Solutions : Magento 2.2.7 and 2.3 Admin Page:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> How&nbsp;to&nbsp;solve&nbsp;blank&nbsp;issue&nbsp;of&nbsp;Magento&nbsp;2.2.7&nbsp;admin&nbsp;page: </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You’ll find this code:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>protected function isPathInDirectories($path, $directories)<br> {<br>     if (!is_array($directories)) {<br>         $directories = (array)$directories;<br>     }<br>     foreach ($directories as $directory) {<br>         if (0 === strpos($this-&gt;fileDriver-&gt;getRealPath($path), $directory)) {<br>             return true;<br>         }<br>     }<br>     return false;<br> }</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Which shall be replaced by the following code</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>protected function isPathInDirectories($path, $directories)<br>\n    {<br>\n        $realPath = str_replace(\'\\\', \'/\', $this-&gt;fileDriver-&gt;getRealPath($path));<br>\n        if (!is_array($directories)) {<br>\n            $directories = (array)$directories;<br>\n        }<br>\n        foreach ($directories as $directory) {<br>\n            if (0 === strpos($realPath, $directory)) {<br>\n                return true;<br>\n            }<br>\n        }<br>\n        return false;<br>\n    }</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>How to solve the Magento 2.3 admin page blank issue:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Navigate to #<strong>/vendor/magento/framework/View/Element/Template/File/Validator.php:114</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Find the below string:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:table -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>1</td><td>$realPath = $this-&gt;fileDriver-&gt;getRealPath($path);</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>and replace it with:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:table -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>1</td><td>$realPath = str_replace(\'\\\\\', \'/\', $this-&gt;fileDriver-&gt;getRealPath($path));</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->', 'Solved: Blank Issue Magento 2.2.7 and 2.3 Admin', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '269-2', '', '', '2021-10-31 06:28:57', '2021-10-31 06:28:57', '', 0, 'https://www.ayushshrestha.com.np/?p=269', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(312, 1, '2021-10-31 06:28:14', '2021-10-31 06:28:14', 'Blank Issue admin magento', 'Blank Issue admin magento', 'Blank Issue admin magento', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', 'blank-issue-admin-magento', '', '', '2021-10-31 06:28:41', '2021-10-31 06:28:41', '', 269, 'https://www.ayushshrestha.com.np/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/blank-issue-admin-magento.png', 0, 'attachment', 'image/png', 0),
(271, 1, '2020-04-18 13:56:31', '2020-04-18 13:56:31', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solved: Blank Issue Magento 2.2.7 and 2.3 Admin</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Magento 2 CMS is an effective platform for the running of e-commerce companies and can be managed via the admin panel. Admin is responsible for the store\'s functionalities and any errors in the admin panel are unacceptable. However, after updating or installing Magento 2.2.7 and Magento 2.3, the clients faced the question of the blank page in the admin panel!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We fixed this problem and have agreed to publish it as a workaround for all Magento 2.2.7 and Magento 2.3 store owners.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you have downloaded or updated the new version recently and face the blank issue of the Magento 2.2.7 and 2.3 admin page, as shown below, follow the solution given in the article.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":270} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.ayushshrestha.com.np/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/magento-blank-admin-1024x574.png\" alt=\"Magento Blank Admin\" class=\"wp-image-270\"/><figcaption>Magento Blank Admin</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Solutions : Magento 2.2.7 and 2.3 Admin Page:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> How to solve blank issue of Magento 2.2.7 admin page: </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You’ll find this code:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>protected function isPathInDirectories($path, $directories)<br> {<br>     if (!is_array($directories)) {<br>         $directories = (array)$directories;<br>     }<br>     foreach ($directories as $directory) {<br>         if (0 === strpos($this->fileDriver->getRealPath($path), $directory)) {<br>             return true;<br>         }<br>     }<br>     return false;<br> }</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Which shall be replaced by the following code</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>protected function isPathInDirectories($path, $directories)<br>\n    {<br>\n        $realPath = str_replace(\'\\\', \'/\', $this-&gt;fileDriver-&gt;getRealPath($path));<br>\n        if (!is_array($directories)) {<br>\n            $directories = (array)$directories;<br>\n        }<br>\n        foreach ($directories as $directory) {<br>\n            if (0 === strpos($realPath, $directory)) {<br>\n                return true;<br>\n            }<br>\n        }<br>\n        return false;<br>\n    }</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>How to solve the Magento 2.3 admin page blank issue:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Navigate to #<strong>/vendor/magento/framework/View/Element/Template/File/Validator.php:114</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Find the below string:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:table -->\n<table class=\"wp-block-table\"><tbody><tr><td>1</td><td>$realPath = $this-&gt;fileDriver-&gt;getRealPath($path);</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>and replace it with:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:table -->\n<table class=\"wp-block-table\"><tbody><tr><td>1</td><td>$realPath = str_replace(\'\\\\\', \'/\', $this-&gt;fileDriver-&gt;getRealPath($path));</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<!-- /wp:table -->', '', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '269-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-04-18 13:56:31', '2020-04-18 13:56:31', '', 269, 'https://www.ayushshrestha.com.np/269-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(274, 1, '2020-05-07 05:25:11', '2020-05-07 05:25:11', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solutions</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>$(\'a&#91;data-toggle=\"tab\"]\').on(\'shown.bs.tab\', function() {   \n  $($(this).attr(\'href\')).find(\'.slider\').slick({\n    dots: true,\n    arrows: true\n  })\n}).first().trigger(\'shown.bs.tab\');</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Demo</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"http://jsfiddle.net/vv4j3uz2/7/\">http://jsfiddle.net/vv4j3uz2/7/</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Sources </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/48400304/slick-slider-zero-width-in-hidden-container-bootstrap-tab\">https://stackoverflow.com/questions/48400304/slick-slider-zero-width-in-hidden-container-bootstrap-tab</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Slick Slider zero width in hidden container (Bootstrap tab)', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'slick-slider-zero-width-in-hidden-container-bootstrap-tab', '', '', '2023-05-04 05:13:15', '2023-05-04 05:13:15', '', 0, 'https://www.ayushshrestha.com.np/?p=274', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(276, 1, '2020-05-07 05:25:11', '2020-05-07 05:25:11', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solutions</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>$(\'a[data-toggle=\"tab\"]\').on(\'shown.bs.tab\', function() {   \n  $($(this).attr(\'href\')).find(\'.slider\').slick({\n    dots: true,\n    arrows: true\n  })\n}).first().trigger(\'shown.bs.tab\');</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Demo</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"http://jsfiddle.net/vv4j3uz2/7/\">http://jsfiddle.net/vv4j3uz2/7/</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Sources </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/48400304/slick-slider-zero-width-in-hidden-container-bootstrap-tab\">https://stackoverflow.com/questions/48400304/slick-slider-zero-width-in-hidden-container-bootstrap-tab</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Slick Slider zero width in hidden container (Bootstrap tab)', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '274-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-05-07 05:25:11', '2020-05-07 05:25:11', '', 274, 'https://www.ayushshrestha.com.np/274-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(281, 1, '2020-08-18 01:56:13', '2020-08-18 01:56:13', 'No Commands defined \"Passport\" Laravel 7', 'No-No Commands defined \"Passport\" Laravel 7-defined-Passport-Laravel 7@2x', 'No Commands defined \"Passport\" Laravel 7', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', 'no-commands-defined-passport-laravel-72x', '', '', '2020-08-18 01:58:00', '2020-08-18 01:58:00', '', 279, 'https://www.ayushshrestha.com.np/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/No-Commands-defined-Passport-Laravel-7@2x.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(282, 1, '2020-08-18 01:58:12', '2020-08-18 01:58:12', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For installing laravel passport make sure you add this line to <strong><em>config/app.php</em></strong> in the providers array (package service providers section):</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Laravel\\Passport\\PassportServiceProvider::class,</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><br>Then install the package and migrate the database</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>composer require laravel/passport<br>php artisan migrate<br>php artisan passport:install</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><br>Clearing out the cache is generally helpful first step when commands are not working, especially when you update anything in the config folder on .env files.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>php artisan config:clear<br>php artisan config:cache</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><br>Config clear removes the configuration cache file. Config cache creates a new configuration cache file with the current settings. Config cache enables faster load times for your apps!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'No Commands defined \"Passport\" Laravel 7', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '279-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-08-18 01:58:12', '2020-08-18 01:58:12', '', 279, 'https://www.ayushshrestha.com.np/279-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(284, 1, '2021-01-16 16:28:30', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You wake up one fine morning, brew some coffee, and sit down at your workstation. \"Shockingly, you find a simple short message on a blank white screen: \"Error Creating a Database Link</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>No matter how many times you refresh the website, you can\'t access it.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Sadly, you are missing the ability to create leads, have conversions, and enjoy sales for each minute that your website is down.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The severity of the situation is severe, but calm your nerves down and do not panic! Keep reading this guide to better understand and learn a realistic approach to fixing a database relation error in WordPress.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You wake up one fine morning, brew some coffee and sit down at your workstation. \"Shockingly, you find a simple short message on a blank white screen: \"Error Creating a Database Link</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>No matter how many times you refresh the website, you can\'t access it.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Sadly, you are missing the ability to create leads, have conversions, and enjoy sales for each minute that your website is down.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The severity of the situation is severe, but calm your nerves down and do not panic! Keep reading this guide to better understand and learn a realistic approach to fixing a database relation error in WordPress.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This error can be triggered by any of the following scenarios:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>It is likely that your login credentials (username and password) have changed. Even if you didn\'t make the adjustment yourself, somehow this would have happened.</li><li>Your database can be compromised if you install a poorly coded plugin.</li><li>A strong traffic spike may be encountered by your website, which is beyond the capability of your server.</li><li>Your WordPress web hosting may be at fault and because of some issue at its end, the database is not running.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I advise you to make a backup before any attempt to fix the error creating a database link in WordPress! To make a backup, you have the following choices:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'How to Repair a WordPress Database Connection?', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2021-01-16 16:28:30', '2021-01-16 16:28:30', '', 0, 'https://www.ayushshrestha.com.np/?p=284', 0, 'post', '', 0),
